    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="162"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J.C.S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the United States Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d162fn1">For the discussion of the subject of this paper by
                        the Combined Chiefs of Staff at their 174th Meeting, September 14, 1944, see
                            <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_331">p. 331</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 452/25</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-08">8 September
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">British Participation in the War Against Japan</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">Reference: <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 452/18<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d162fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_244">p. 244</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The United States Chiefs of Staff accept the British proposal in <gloss
                        target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 452/18 for the formation of a British Empire
                    task force under a British commander, consisting of British, Australian, and New
                    Zealand land, sea and air forces to operate in the Southwest Pacific Theater
                    under General MacArthur’s supreme command. It is noted that this will enable the
                    British Fleet to be well placed to reenforce the U.S. Pacific Fleet if this
                    should later be desired.</p>
            </div>
